      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version-controlled; regression test suite executed prior to simulation campaign with zero critical failures.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 employed under an ISO 13485-aligned software lifecycle. Version control records, regression test logs, and release notes reviewed. All 847 regression cases passed. Achieved level 2 exceeds MRL 2 requirement of level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy test against analytical Couette flow solution demonstrates observed order within 10% of theoretical second-order convergence.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver. Observed spatial order 1.94 (theoretical 2.0); temporal order 1.97. Benchmark confirms correct implementation of discretization scheme for blood-analogue viscosity model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI for primary hemolysis QoI (volume-averaged scalar shear stress) must be below 2% on the production mesh, confirming mesh-independent results.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (coarse 2.1 M, medium 5.8 M, fine 14.3 M cells) were evaluated. GCI between medium and fine meshes is 3.7% for the volume-averaged scalar shear stress — above the 2% acceptance threshold. The team elected to proceed using the medium mesh on schedule grounds, citing that the 3.7% GCI is within engineering tolerance for relative comparisons. However, the formal acceptance criterion is not met, and the production mesh cannot be certified as operating in the asymptotic convergence regime for the primary hemolysis QoI. Achieved level 1 falls below the required level 2 for MRL 2 at High decision consequence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate ±2%, rotational speed ±10 RPM, fluid viscosity ±3%) replicated in simulation within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Flow loop operating conditions documented in laboratory notebook LN-2023-047. Inlet velocity profiles measured by LDV at pump inlet plane; rotational speed logged by optical tachometer at 1 Hz throughout each test. Temperature-corrected viscosity of blood analogue (40% glycerin-water) matched to within 1.8% of target. Boundary condition fidelity confirmed at level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Normalized RMSE between predicted and measured velocity fields (PIV) ≤ 5%; predicted hemolysis index within ±15% of bench measurement across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "PIV comparison at mid-impeller plane: normalized RMSE 4.8% at 3000 RPM and 4.6% at 4500 RPM, meeting the 5% threshold. Hemolysis index predictions within ±11.2% of bench measurements across all five operating points. Quantitative agreement supports level 3 designation. Uncertainty in PIV measurement (±2.1% of local velocity) propagated through comparison metric."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical endpoint; secondary QoI (scalar shear stress distribution) is mechanistically linked to the power-law hemolysis model.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the regulatory acceptance criterion for Class II CPB devices per FDA guidance. Scalar shear stress is the input to the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model, providing a direct mechanistic chain from CFD output to hemolysis prediction. QoI relevance confirmed at required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid properties, and operating range span the design space of the COU; no extrapolation beyond validated envelope required.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry class as the COU device. Operating range (2 to 6 L/min, 2500 to 5000 RPM) encompasses all five COU flow-speed combinations. Blood analogue viscosity within 8% of clinical blood viscosity range. Validation relevance confirmed at level 2; no extrapolation required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence to 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance below 0.01% of inlet mass flow.",
      "rationale": "Continuity and momentum residuals converged to 1e-6 within 2500 iterations for all steady-state operating points. Mass imbalance 0.003% of inlet mass flow. Iterative convergence confirmed at required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; checklist of 24 setup parameters signed off prior to production run.",
      "rationale": "Independent analyst review conducted per internal procedure SOP-CFD-007. All 24 checklist items verified: turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), wall treatment (enhanced wall function y+ 1–3), rotating reference frame formulation, and hemolysis model constants. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison to published benchmark data for confined rotating flows; hemolysis model constants sourced from peer-reviewed calibration study.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on Hariharan et al. (2011) benchmark demonstrating superior performance for centrifugal pump flows versus standard k-epsilon. Power-law hemolysis constants (C=3.62e-5, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) from Giersiepen et al. (1990) calibration. Model form uncertainty acknowledged as primary contributor to hemolysis prediction uncertainty; level 1 appropriate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
